I"n<p>As usual toward the end of the semester, my students begin working in earnest on their final projects. And as usual, this results in my selective amnesia about <a href="http://www.census.gov">census.gov</a> being ruptured yet again. Looking for a way out, I turned to <a href="https://twitter.com/AmeliaMN/status/798620977202663424">twitter</a> and got some good recommendations. In case it’s useful to other teachers/people, I’ll share my thoughts.</p>

